column5: Anyone have a source for these jig heads on our side of the border? Been looking and can't find them anywhere.  Thanks guys.
They do not catch esox...keep looking  Have you called JB's?
yeah JBs has them, I would think Grimsby tackle would too?
Yeah they're useless aren't they?  I did call them yeah...
Nope neither place has them in stock.
Jigs  Are these them?  Im curious!
Champane kisses and caviar dreams, it's what all the well to do esox anglers are using. I suppose you use those peasant jigs?  Hmmmmph........................ :walks away with nose in the air:
Put Dawg to work on replicating 'em.  JF
Not unless they're solid titanium. They're a couple bucks each.

"YES IT'S LIFESTYLES OF THE POOR AND ANONYMOUS! HERE WE ARE IN THE DISGUSTING NORTHERN ABODE OF THE INFAMOUS DRIFTER_016!! MUST BE VERY CAREFUL NOT TO COME IN CONTACT WITH ANY SURFACES!! WHY AM I YELLING? I HAVE NO IDEA!"
